Police in Mpeketoni, Lamu, are holding a 36-year-old man found in possession of an eight-foot-long python skin.  Peter Kahoro was arrested on Sunday by police as he was carrying the skin.The officers were on regular patrols in Majembeni village.  Lamu police commander Muchangi Kioi yesterday said Kahoro will be charged with poaching. “He was in the process of having the python skin transported for sale outside of Lamu county,” he said. Meanwhile, police in Lamu are investigating the discovery of four crates of medicine found on the shores of the Indian Ocean in Shella are, on Sunday. The drugs weighed more than 20kg and were discovered by fishermen. “We suspect someone had stolen the drugs from the hospital and hidden them,” Kioi said.